## 6. Product Principles

### 6.1 Credibility First

The site must feel reliable, factual, and structured. Nothing should feel sloppy, sensational, or unverified.

### 6.2 Mobile First

A large share of traffic will likely come from mobile and social. The mobile experience must not feel secondary.

### 6.3 Visually Premium

The platform should feel more like a polished publication than a student project or basic WordPress blog.

### 6.4 Fast and Lightweight

Users should be able to access content quickly even in lower-bandwidth conditions.

### 6.5 Easy to Scan

Articles, categories, and homepage sections should be designed for fast understanding.

### 6.6 Opportunity as a Core Pillar

Scholarships, internships, programs, and deadlines should be treated as a first-class content type, not an afterthought.

### 6.7 Strong Identity

The website should be recognizably EdLight News, with a clear editorial voice and visual system.

