## 10. Category Pages

Each major category should have its own dedicated page.

### Category Page Requirements

* strong heading and visual identity
* featured top story
* article feed/grid below
* filtering or sorting where relevant
* pagination or infinite scroll depending on implementation
* optional subtopics/tags

### Priority Categories

* Haiti
* World
* Education
* Business & Economy
* Technology
* Opportunities
* Explainers

The category pages should help users feel the platform is deep, not shallow.

---

## 11. Article Page Requirements

The article page is the product core after the homepage.

### Primary Objectives

* maximize readability
* establish credibility
* support content sharing
* drive continued browsing

### Article Header

Must include:

* headline
* subheadline or dek (optional but recommended)
* category label
* author or EdLight News attribution
* publish date
* updated date if relevant
* hero image

### Article Body Requirements

* clean typography
* generous spacing
* readable width
* embedded media support
* pull quotes or highlighted facts optional
* subheadings for long pieces
* links to related content when useful

### Article Footer / Below Article

Should include:

* related stories
* related opportunities where relevant
* share options
* tags/topics
* author card or EdLight News attribution block
* next/previous story suggestion

### Reading Experience Principles

* no clutter
* no overly aggressive popups
* no distracting design patterns
* strong contrast and legibility
* easy return to homepage/category flow

---

## 12. Opportunities Content Type

This is a critical differentiator for EdLight News.

### Why It Matters

Many users will visit not only for news but for real opportunities. This content should be easier to discover than on traditional media sites.

### Opportunity Card Requirements

Each opportunity listing should show:

* title
* type (scholarship, internship, competition, etc.)
* location or eligibility region if relevant
* deadline
* short summary
* image or visual marker
* CTA to learn more

### Opportunity Detail Page Requirements

Must include:

* title
* summary
* eligibility
* deadline
* application link or instructions
* benefits/value proposition
* region/audience
* source or origin
* tags
* related opportunities

### Opportunity Sorting / Filtering

Recommended filters:

* deadline
* opportunity type
* region
* education level
* field/industry

This section should feel practical and useful, not hidden inside the broader news archive.

